---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const githubUrl = 'https://github.com/maxistar/Voice-Inbox';
const releaseUrl = `${githubUrl}/releases`;
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
const androidScreenshot = `${base}/screenshots/android-main.jpg`;
---
<Layout
  title="Voice notes to Markdown"
  description="Voice Inbox is a local-first app for turning accumulated voice recordings into a Markdown or plain-text inbox. Android is ready; iOS is an active MVP."
>
  <style>
    .hero {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.05fr) minmax(280px, 0.75fr);
      gap: 42px;
      align-items: center;
      min-height: 560px;
    }
    .hero-copy p {
      max-width: 640px;
      font-size: 1.12rem;
    }
    .hero-visual {
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 28px;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #eff6ff, #ffffff);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      padding: 18px;
    }
    .screenshot-shell {
      border: 10px solid #111827;
      border-radius: 28px;
      background: #f8fafc;
      overflow: hidden;
      max-height: 620px;
    }
    .screenshot-shell img {
      display: block;
      width: 100%;
      height: auto;
    }
    .caption {
      margin: 14px 0 0;
      color: var(--soft);
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .platform-card {
      display: grid;
      gap: 12px;
    }
    .status-badge {
      display: inline-flex;
      width: fit-content;
      border-radius: 999px;
      padding: 5px 10px;
      color: var(--accent-strong);
      background: var(--accent-soft);
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      font-weight: 850;
    }
    .flow {
      counter-reset: flow;
    }
    .flow .card {
      position: relative;
      padding-left: 58px;
    }
    .flow .card::before {
      counter-increment: flow;
      content: counter(flow);
      position: absolute;
      left: 20px;
      top: 22px;
      width: 26px;
      height: 26px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      color: white;
      background: var(--accent);
      display: grid;
      place-items: center;
      font-weight: 900;
    }
    .requirements {
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 8px;
      background: var(--surface);
      padding: 24px;
    }
    @media (max-width: 860px) {
      .hero {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        min-height: auto;
      }
    }
  </style>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Local-first voice note transcription</p>
      <h1>Turn voice notes into a Markdown inbox.</h1>
      <p>
        Voice Inbox turns accumulated recordings into a readable text inbox. Android has the mature
        folder workflow today; iOS now has an active MVP for importing, previewing, transcribing,
        and appending individual recordings locally.
      </p>
      <div class="button-row">
        <a class="button primary" href={releaseUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Download from GitHub Releases</a>
        <a class="button" href={githubUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">View source</a>
        <a class="button" href={`${base}/setup/`}>Setup guide</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-visual" aria-label="Voice Inbox app preview">
      <div class="screenshot-shell">
        <img src={androidScreenshot} alt="Voice Inbox Android app showing scanned audio files and playback actions" />
      </div>
      <p class="caption">Android workflow screenshot. iOS MVP is evolving alongside the shared core.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Platform status</p>
    <h2>Android is ready; iOS is catching up fast.</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card platform-card">
        <span class="status-badge">Android ready</span>
        <h3>Full folder workflow</h3>
        <p>Scan a selected audio folder, preview recordings, transcribe individual files or all New files, append to Markdown or text, retry failures, and schedule best-effort background runs.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card platform-card">
        <span class="status-badge">iOS MVP</span>
        <h3>Manual import workflow</h3>
        <p>Import audio files, preview them, download the speech model, transcribe locally, show recognized text, and append output. Folder automation and scheduling are still in progress.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card platform-card">
        <span class="status-badge">Shared core</span>
        <h3>Kotlin Multiplatform foundation</h3>
        <p>Catalog and transcription use cases are moving into shared code so Android and iOS can converge without hiding platform-specific storage and background limitations.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="eyebrow">What it does</p>
    <h2>Built for accumulated recordings, not live dictation.</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Incremental folder transcription</h3>
        <p>Select one folder, review discovered recordings, and process only files that are new or changed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Local recognition</h3>
        <p>After the first model download, recognition runs on device instead of sending audio to an app cloud service.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Markdown or plain text output</h3>
        <p>Each successful note is appended to an existing writable <code>.md</code> or <code>.txt</code> document.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Preview before processing</h3>
        <p>Play audio files from the list before deciding to transcribe them.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Scheduled processing</h3>
        <p>On Android, optionally ask the app to run scheduled transcription around your chosen time. Exact execution is not guaranteed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Transparent history</h3>
        <p>Processed and failed files stay visible, and failed files can be retried individually.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Workflow</p>
    <h2>From recordings to notes in five steps.</h2>
    <div class="grid flow">
      <div class="card"><h3>Install the model</h3><p>Download and verify the speech model on first launch.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Select output</h3><p>Choose an existing writable Markdown or text file.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Select recordings</h3><p>Pick the folder that contains your audio notes.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Review New files</h3><p>Preview recordings and check what will be processed.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Transcribe all</h3><p>Append one entry per successful file with filename, recording time, and recognized text.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section requirements">
    <p class="eyebrow">Requirements</p>
    <h2>Designed for local, on-device recognition.</h2>
    <p>
      Android requires Android 7.0 (API 24) or later on an ARM64 device. Both Android and the iOS MVP
      need network access for the first model download and enough free storage for model installation.
    </p>
    <div class="button-row">
      <a class="button primary" href={releaseUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Get the APK</a>
      <a class="button" href={`${base}/faq/`}>Read FAQ</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
